This is the \emph{folding pattern} of $L$.

The folding pattern carries some additional information, that we can
make visible. We know that $L$ restricted to $R$ is an orientation
reversing homeomorphism that fixes $X$. Moreover, it maps the set of
basic points bijectively onto the set of turning and postturning
points. Thus, we know which symbol of the folding pattern is mapped to
which one (see Figure~\ref{fig:fpmap}).

